$ VBA - language: on error goto

The `on error goto <label>` statement enables an → development/languages/VBA/language/error_handling[error handler].

The `on error goto 0` statement disables an *error handler* so that the program stops with an error message if an error is encountered. This is the default.

`on error resume next` doesn't do anything special if an error occures: it resumes with execution in the next statement.

